16:24.400 --> 16:26.443
but she interfered

16:26.527 --> 16:28.487
because she didn't want
the church to have it.

16:28.571 --> 16:30.572
She didn't like that pastor.

16:30.657 --> 16:34.076
He wore
Bermuda shorts
on his day off.

16:34.160 --> 16:35.869
(pastor)
Friends and loved ones...

16:35.953 --> 16:38.038
Everybody in town

16:38.122 --> 16:40.082
knew that
Mr. And Mrs. Nugent
weren't exactly friends

16:40.166 --> 16:42.417
with their
son Dwayne Junior
and his family.

16:42.502 --> 16:45.045
He was a doctor
out in Middleton,
almost never came to visit.

16:45.129 --> 16:47.464
One of his daughters
had actually sued
her grandparents

16:47.548 --> 16:49.800
trying to get at
the money in that trust.

16:49.884 --> 16:53.095
That made her so mad
she never spoke to
any of them again.

16:53.179 --> 16:55.055
Let us pray.

16:55.139 --> 16:59.518
Marjorie Nugent.
She was...

16:59.602 --> 17:03.980
not a very nice lady
and her nose was
so high

17:04.065 --> 17:06.233
she'd drown
in a rainstorm.

17:06.317 --> 17:09.903
Mrs. Margy, she was
the kind of person

17:09.987 --> 17:12.864
that I believe
she was born old.

17:12.949 --> 17:14.991
She was just born
with this prune face.

17:15.076 --> 17:17.243
That's pretty
much the impression
people got from her.

17:17.328 --> 17:20.122
I got a buddy
of mine, Louie.

17:20.205 --> 17:23.208
He's a decent fellow
I work for.

17:23.291 --> 17:25.627
Mrs. Nugent took
a broom to his
ass one day.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.878
Would you like me to get up
and do the back in there?

17:27.964 --> 17:30.132
- Get out.
- Ooh.

17:30.216 --> 17:33.301
[Inaudible]

17:33.386 --> 17:34.553
Oh.

17:37.890 --> 17:39.766
- Beautiful service.
- Thank you.

17:39.851 --> 17:42.894
- I'll see you on Sunday.
- Thank you very much.

17:42.979 --> 17:45.647
[Deep sigh]

17:45.732 --> 17:47.774
He was great
with the D-L-O-Ls.

17:47.859 --> 17:50.360
That's what we all called
the "dear little old ladies."

17:50.445 --> 17:52.988
All the widows in town
had crushes on Bernie.

17:53.072 --> 17:55.866
Just thought
I'd bring you a hankie.

17:55.950 --> 17:57.701
Oh, yeah, old Bernie.

17:57.785 --> 18:00.537
He loved to hug and
kiss on those
older women.

18:00.621 --> 18:06.168
At his age now,
they were lucky to get
the time of day from him.

18:10.256 --> 18:15.385
[Deep sigh]

18:15.470 --> 18:17.137
Hi.

18:17.221 --> 18:19.848
Hi, Mrs. Nugent,
I just, uh...

18:19.932 --> 18:21.725
wanted you to know
I was thinking about you.

18:21.809 --> 18:24.895
- These times can be hard.
- Oh, thank you.

18:24.979 --> 18:26.563
Okay.

18:26.647 --> 18:28.190
I never asked him
to do this and

18:28.274 --> 18:30.317
he wasn't getting
paid to do it,

18:30.401 --> 18:32.110
but he would always stop by
and check on the widows

18:32.195 --> 18:33.862
after he'd done
their husbands' funerals.

18:33.946 --> 18:35.614
He just really
cared about them.

18:35.698 --> 18:37.908
I mean, that guy was
just a sweet guy,

18:37.992 --> 18:39.826
and they just
loved him to death.

18:47.710 --> 18:48.627
[Knocking]

18:49.879 --> 18:51.671
Room service.

18:51.756 --> 18:54.007
Hi, I'm just dropping
by again, Mrs. Nugent,

18:54.091 --> 18:55.258
to pay my respects.

18:55.343 --> 18:57.093
I brought you some soaps

18:57.178 --> 18:58.929
and a little bubble bath
to soothe you in the tub,

18:59.013 --> 19:01.556
and some chocolate cupcakes
for a late night snack.

19:01.641 --> 19:03.099
Come in.

19:03.184 --> 19:05.769
Oh!
That... would be
my pleasure.

19:05.853 --> 19:08.480
[Clears throat]

19:08.564 --> 19:09.815
[Slurps]

19:09.899 --> 19:11.775
[Classical music playing]

19:11.859 --> 19:13.568
In high school I wanted
to be an evangelist

19:13.653 --> 19:16.404
to save the souls
of my fellow students.

19:16.489 --> 19:18.865
A lot of them
were starting
to drink and smoke

19:18.950 --> 19:21.117
and ride motorcycles

19:21.202 --> 19:24.037
and have premarital sexual
experiences and all that.

19:24.121 --> 19:25.622
- Oh, yes please!
- Here you go, Bernie.

19:25.706 --> 19:28.750
Thank you, Esmeralda.

19:28.835 --> 19:30.335
When.

19:30.419 --> 19:34.005
Miss Marjorie?

19:34.090 --> 19:36.508
[Sigh]

19:36.592 --> 19:38.051
One time I got
four teenagers

19:38.135 --> 19:40.720
to re-dedicate
their lives to Jesus,

19:40.805 --> 19:44.558
but eventually I realized
I was meant for other
equally important things.

19:44.642 --> 19:46.393
Oh, please, Bernie,

19:46.477 --> 19:49.062
touching all those
cold bloated bodies.
Please!

19:49.146 --> 19:52.232
Don't you think you
were meant to do
something more?

19:52.316 --> 19:53.984
No, no, no, no,
Mrs. Nugent.

19:54.068 --> 19:56.111
It isn't bad at all.

19:56.195 --> 19:58.655
Their souls are
already with the Lord
by the time I'm involved.

19:58.739 --> 20:00.448
It's just my
way to serve

20:00.533 --> 20:01.867
and show respect
for the lives they led

20:01.951 --> 20:03.118
and comfort all
the loved ones

20:03.202 --> 20:04.244
that they
leave behind.

20:04.328 --> 20:08.456
[Deep sigh]
Well.

20:08.541 --> 20:11.751
And some day, if I'm lucky,
many many years from now,

20:11.836 --> 20:14.796
I will give you such
a beautiful funeral...

20:14.881 --> 20:17.966
with all the roses
in East Texas.

20:18.050 --> 20:22.470
I know it'll be the event
of the season in Carthage.

20:22.555 --> 20:24.848
You know, I think
that Bernie was
the one

20:24.932 --> 20:30.478
that got Marjorie
back to church after
her husband died.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.314
(female voice)
Well, I know
the Bible says

20:32.398 --> 20:34.858
Jesus turned
water into wine,

20:34.942 --> 20:38.278
but it didn't say
liquor store wine.

20:38.362 --> 20:42.073
It had to have been
non-alcoholic wine,

20:42.158 --> 20:44.993
because it didn't
have time to ferment.

20:45.077 --> 20:47.329
If Jesus could
walk on the water,

20:47.413 --> 20:50.749
he could make any
kind of wine he
wanted to.

20:50.833 --> 20:52.250
Fermented or not.

20:52.335 --> 20:54.002
Right on the spot.

20:54.086 --> 20:55.170
(male voice)
Morning, ladies.

20:55.254 --> 20:57.547
Sorry to interrupt.

20:57.632 --> 21:00.008
Mrs. Marjorie, it is
so good to have you
with us this morning.

21:00.092 --> 21:02.677
I just want to put
a bug in your ear now.

21:02.762 --> 21:05.138
Many of you know
we're hoping to
start construction

21:05.222 --> 21:07.140
on our new
prayer wing soon.

21:07.224 --> 21:09.184
[Several]
Mmm.

21:09.268 --> 21:10.852
Well, I'm hoping I
can count on a few
of you

21:10.937 --> 21:13.355
to join
the fundraising
committee. Okay?

21:13.439 --> 21:15.273
Think about it, now.
God bless you.

21:15.358 --> 21:19.819
[All singing]
♪ This is my story
This is my song ♪

21:19.904 --> 21:24.157
♪ Praising my savior
All the day long ♪

21:24.241 --> 21:28.453
♪ This is my story
This is my song ♪

21:28.537 --> 21:32.707
♪ Praising my savior
All the day long ♪

21:32.792 --> 21:37.712
[sings alone]
♪ Perfect submission
Perfect delight ♪

21:37.797 --> 21:42.050
♪ Visions of rapture
Now burst on my sight ♪

21:42.134 --> 21:46.388
♪ Angels descending
Bring from above ♪

21:46.472 --> 21:50.517
♪ Echoes of mercy
Whispers of love ♪

21:50.601 --> 21:54.813
♪ This is my story
This is my song ♪

21:54.897 --> 21:59.192
♪ Praising my savior
All the day long ♪

21:59.276 --> 22:02.404
(Mrs. Nugent)
Uh-uh, no,
we'll take my car.

22:02.488 --> 22:04.239
No, I insist.

22:04.323 --> 22:07.409
Don't be silly, Bernie.

22:07.493 --> 22:09.119
Good, I'll see you
Saturday afternoon.

22:09.203 --> 22:10.912
I'm... I'm looking
forward to it, too.

22:10.997 --> 22:15.500
Okay, Mrs. Nugent, bye.

22:18.796 --> 22:22.173
Oh, so sweet.

22:22.258 --> 22:26.011
That was Bernie Tiede, the
assistant funeral director.

22:26.095 --> 22:29.180
He's very sweet
and very nice to me.

22:29.265 --> 22:33.935
Can't think of anyone
who's been that nice
to me in 50 years.

22:34.020 --> 22:35.937
Now, you!

22:36.022 --> 22:37.605
You've got two minutes
to explain these accounts
to me.

22:37.690 --> 22:39.315
Or three minutes from now

22:39.400 --> 22:41.276
I just might get myself
another stockbroker.

22:41.360 --> 22:43.570
I can explain everything,
Miss Marjorie.

22:43.654 --> 22:45.697
It's a very simple
case of them changing
their accounting statements.

22:45.781 --> 22:48.992
They changed
their formatting,
it's re-formatted...

22:49.076 --> 22:50.744
in a different format.

22:50.828 --> 22:53.038
Hey, listen.

22:53.122 --> 22:56.041
I couldn't help but hear
the end of that conversation.

22:56.125 --> 22:58.043
I gotta tell you, Bernie,

22:58.127 --> 22:59.711
you have got to be
about the bravest
man in this town.

22:59.795 --> 23:02.088
She isn't all that mean
like everyone says.

23:02.173 --> 23:03.631
Now you sure
about that?

23:03.716 --> 23:05.467
Well, she doesn't
have anyone, Don.

23:05.551 --> 23:08.470
She's a very
Ionely person.
She needs someone.

23:08.554 --> 23:10.388
I've asked her
to accompany me
this Saturday

23:10.473 --> 23:12.974
to the Van Clyburn
Piano Competition
in Fort Worth.

23:13.059 --> 23:15.310
Well, have fun.

23:15.394 --> 23:17.771
Ain't like she's
the richest widow
in town.

23:17.855 --> 23:19.731
Hell, maybe she'll
even pay for everything.

23:19.815 --> 23:21.900
- Don!
- Hey...

23:21.984 --> 23:24.652
And if she does offer
to pay for everything,

23:24.737 --> 23:27.447
order up a couple
of them bottles
of Dom Perignon.

23:27.531 --> 23:28.990
You get her
liquored up,

23:29.075 --> 23:30.075
[whispering]
You might get lucky.

23:30.159 --> 23:32.452
No, Don!

23:32.536 --> 23:35.747
He sincerely believed that...

23:35.831 --> 23:39.125
it was better to give
than to receive.

23:39.210 --> 23:41.294
Well, Bernie had
a problem with money.

23:41.378 --> 23:44.631
He was generous.
Some folks say
overly generous.

23:44.715 --> 23:47.217
What he was
was a buy-aholic.

23:47.301 --> 23:49.844
And, uh... hell, he'd
walk into a store,

23:49.929 --> 23:52.347
seen something he liked,
he'd buy the store

23:52.431 --> 23:54.516
out of every goddamn
item he wanted

23:54.600 --> 23:56.017
and give the shit away.

23:56.102 --> 23:57.852
And that's crazy.

23:57.937 --> 23:59.687
But that Bernie,
he liked to make
people smile.

23:59.772 --> 24:01.356
He wanted friends.

24:01.440 --> 24:03.024
Acceptance, I guess,
is what you call it.

24:03.109 --> 24:05.735
And Bernie could do
just about anything.

24:05.820 --> 24:09.280
I mean, he
could hang wallpaper
in people's houses,

24:09.365 --> 24:11.950
and I've never seen
any man do this,

24:12.034 --> 24:14.285
but he could make
curtains for people

24:14.370 --> 24:16.496
and he was
the head honcho

24:16.580 --> 24:18.581
for the Chamber of Commerce

24:18.666 --> 24:20.750
Christmas
decorating committee.

24:20.835 --> 24:23.586
That's a big thing
in Carthage, too,
a big thing.

24:23.671 --> 24:25.421
Bernie was really smart.

24:25.506 --> 24:28.091
He helped people do
their tax returns,
you know,

24:28.175 --> 24:30.009
financial counseling...

24:30.094 --> 24:31.928
Anything that you
pay for on the job

24:32.012 --> 24:34.097
that the company,
the oil company

24:34.181 --> 24:36.266
doesn't reimburse you for,
that's a tax deduction.

24:36.350 --> 24:39.394
So, for instance, Toby,
these work coveralls,

24:39.478 --> 24:40.895
did the company
provide you with these?

24:40.980 --> 24:42.605
No, we got
to buy our own.

24:42.690 --> 24:45.150
Bingo. That is
a tax deduction.

24:45.234 --> 24:47.068
And how about
your lunch buckets

24:47.153 --> 24:48.695
and your steel
toe workboots,
they give you those?

24:48.779 --> 24:50.738
- Why, hell no.
- That's what I thought.

24:50.823 --> 24:52.407
- You kidding me?
- U h-uh.

24:52.491 --> 24:54.242
That's tax deduction
number two and three.

24:54.326 --> 24:56.327
(male voice)
Thank you, Sheriff Huckabee.

24:56.412 --> 24:58.705
You're listening to KGAS,
the heartbeat of East Texas.

24:58.789 --> 25:01.207
Now before we
get to the school
cafeteria menu,

25:01.292 --> 25:03.877
and the wedding
anniversaries
for the week,

25:03.961 --> 25:07.380
here's Bernie Tiede
from Leggett Funeral Home.

25:07.464 --> 25:09.465
Thank you, Jerry.

25:09.550 --> 25:11.301
As some of you
are already aware,

25:11.385 --> 25:13.261
Mr. Harvey Gunnolds
left this world
all too soon

25:13.345 --> 25:15.889
this past
Wednesday after a
brief hospital stay.

25:15.973 --> 25:18.057
I used to love having
him on the air.

25:18.142 --> 25:22.395
I mean, every Friday
people would tune in
just to hear Bernie.

25:22.479 --> 25:24.647
And when he
did the obituaries,

25:24.732 --> 25:28.151
it wasn't like a so-and-so
was survived by so-and-so
kind of thing.

25:28.235 --> 25:30.320
It was... let's see
if I can remember...

25:30.404 --> 25:33.698
Left in sorrow
to mourn the passing
of the beloved Mr. Gunnolds

25:33.782 --> 25:36.242
are Mima Gunnolds,
his mother, Georgia...

25:36.327 --> 25:39.996
And the way he would
make them "look good"
in death,

25:40.080 --> 25:42.165
well, he'd make
them sound good, too.

25:42.249 --> 25:44.751
Like Gunnolds was a drunk,

25:44.835 --> 25:46.961
always startin' shit
wherever he went.

25:47.046 --> 25:49.797
He finally got himself
killed in a pool hall.

25:49.882 --> 25:52.300
Now how do you say
something nice about
somebody like that?

25:52.384 --> 25:55.637
Well, to Bernie,
it was, "He was known..."

25:55.721 --> 25:57.555
- for his social
engagements and his...

25:57.640 --> 25:59.140
conversational abilities...

25:59.225 --> 26:02.268
A kid would wrap
his car around a tree

26:02.353 --> 26:04.103
and with Bernie
it was...

26:04.188 --> 26:06.814
- and yet, death slipped
up on young Mr. Shotwell,

26:06.899 --> 26:08.816
as gentle
as a fallen mist.

26:08.901 --> 26:15.365
[Crowd murmuring]

26:15.449 --> 26:17.575
(female voice)
What happened?

26:17.660 --> 26:20.787
[Inaudible dialog]

26:28.545 --> 26:31.339
I regret to inform you

26:31.423 --> 26:36.010
that four of your classmates
have just been killed.

26:36.095 --> 26:37.720
Now this is gonna
happen to you

26:37.805 --> 26:41.266
if you drink and drive.

26:41.350 --> 26:44.769
Is this what you want
to happen to you?

26:44.853 --> 26:47.855
(female voice)
It didn't make no
difference what it was

26:47.940 --> 26:50.525
or who ask it, if it was
good for the community,

26:50.609 --> 26:52.527
Bernie'd give
it all he had.

26:52.611 --> 26:54.737
All the time.

26:54.822 --> 26:57.198
He was very serious
about his commitment
to Carthage.

26:57.283 --> 26:59.200
Life is so beautiful,

26:59.285 --> 27:01.035
every moment a miracle,

27:01.120 --> 27:03.037
and yet in
a blink it's gone.

27:03.122 --> 27:05.832
Too young.
[Inaudible]

27:05.916 --> 27:08.167
[Shouts to crowd]
Too young!

27:08.252 --> 27:12.005
Oh, he really had
a way of bringing
the community together.

27:12.089 --> 27:14.257
Not just at
the funerals
and at the church,

27:14.341 --> 27:18.261
he organized
a "Beautify Carthage" campaign,

27:18.345 --> 27:21.389
and he put on
the very first
East Texas art festival

27:21.473 --> 27:24.309
and invited artists
from all around
the region

27:24.393 --> 27:26.644
to display their works.

27:38.365 --> 27:40.700
[Inaudible]

27:40.784 --> 27:42.660
Are these all...?

27:42.745 --> 27:44.037
I'm sorry to stop you,
are these all done
with that...

27:44.121 --> 27:45.955
the, uh, what's
that called?

27:46.040 --> 27:47.248
It's all chain saw.

27:47.333 --> 27:49.917
How do you do that?

27:50.002 --> 27:52.295
I wake up in the morning
with an idea

27:52.379 --> 27:54.589
and cut away everything
that ain't that idea.

27:54.673 --> 27:56.132
Can I talk to you
at some time?

27:56.216 --> 27:58.009
- Do you have a card?
- Yeah.

27:58.093 --> 27:59.635
Because I have
an idea I would
love to commission.

27:59.720 --> 28:01.471
I don't know if you
work that way, but...

28:01.555 --> 28:03.598
Look at that card, he
put it on a piece
of wood.

28:03.682 --> 28:05.558
- I'm gonna call you.
- Alright.

28:05.642 --> 28:07.602
- You're a gem.
- Thank you.

28:07.686 --> 28:08.895
Thank you.
Okay.

28:08.979 --> 28:10.480
- See you later.
- Bye.

28:10.564 --> 28:12.273
Oh, yeah, Bernie
took her everywhere.

28:12.358 --> 28:17.028
He took her to the
Van Clyburn Competition,

28:17.112 --> 28:18.946
took her up to
the junior college

28:19.031 --> 28:21.324
to see some of
the rehearsals of shows

28:21.408 --> 28:22.867
that he was working on.

28:22.951 --> 28:25.119
Oh, yeah, he always
had Mrs. Nugent.

28:25.204 --> 28:30.666
♪ I've never
Been in love before ♪

28:30.751 --> 28:34.087
♪ Now all at once it's you ♪

28:34.171 --> 28:39.550
♪ It's you forever more ♪

28:39.635 --> 28:44.680
♪ I've never been
In love before ♪

28:44.765 --> 28:48.017
♪ I thought my
Heart was safe ♪

28:48.102 --> 28:52.146
(female voice)
He had come to a production
in a local theater,

28:52.231 --> 28:53.815
and he thought
it could be better

28:53.899 --> 28:56.317
so he volunteered
to help out

28:56.402 --> 29:00.571
and pretty soon
he was the musical
director for one show,

29:00.656 --> 29:02.407
a director in another one,

29:02.491 --> 29:05.076
and an actor
in almost all
of them.

29:05.160 --> 29:07.245
He just had a real
knack for drama.

29:07.329 --> 29:13.167
♪ Please forgive this
Helpless haze I'm in ♪

29:13.252 --> 29:16.546
♪ I've really never been ♪

29:16.630 --> 29:22.343
♪ In love before ♪

29:22.428 --> 29:27.974
♪♪

29:28.058 --> 29:33.438
(girl singing)
♪ I've never been
In love before ♪

29:33.522 --> 29:36.357
♪ Now all
I want to be ♪♪

29:36.442 --> 29:38.860
I saw them at
a restaurant one time.

29:38.944 --> 29:41.571
They was out to lunch together,
and he reached over and kissed
her on the cheek.

29:41.655 --> 29:44.365
But it wasn't a kiss like
you give your momma
or your grandma.

29:44.450 --> 29:47.118
It was more of a romantic,
sexual kiss to me, you know?

29:47.202 --> 29:51.164
He had that graoning sound
in the back of his voice.
It was kinda strange.

29:51.248 --> 29:53.166
It just didn't
look right to me.

29:53.250 --> 29:56.627
The word was
it wasn't a week
after the funeral

29:56.712 --> 30:02.383
Mrs. Nugent gave Bernie
Mr. Nugent's $ 12,000
Rolex watch.

30:02.468 --> 30:06.304
Hell, for that kinda
money, I bet he
did kiss her.

30:06.388 --> 30:09.515
In a small town,
people will always

30:09.600 --> 30:11.976
suspect the worst
of someone.

30:12.060 --> 30:14.854
But they'll also
suspect the best.

30:14.938 --> 30:18.649
So we just thought
they were companions.

30:18.734 --> 30:20.735
Look, it was widely assumed

30:20.819 --> 30:22.236
that Mrs. Nugent
was paying Bernie

30:22.321 --> 30:25.698
to "accompany her" places.

30:25.782 --> 30:27.492
Oh, I'd
estimate they spent

30:27.576 --> 30:29.285
