I was taking it
to get it fixed.

47:18.294 --> 47:20.128
Let me talk to
her, okay Carl?

47:20.213 --> 47:21.838
Don't go getting
a new job just yet.

47:21.923 --> 47:26.676
Okay. But I ain't
going back up there.

47:26.761 --> 47:28.261
Not today anyway.

47:28.346 --> 47:30.430
I don't blame you.

47:30.515 --> 47:33.433
I will get to the bottom
of it and I will call
you back. Okay?

47:33.518 --> 47:34.935
So sorry about this.

47:35.019 --> 47:36.186
Alright.

47:40.691 --> 47:45.028
Oh, you just pop
up whenever it's
convenient for you!

47:45.112 --> 47:47.906
Just when you think
it's fine for you,

47:47.990 --> 47:50.283
you come! Well, fine
fine, fine, fine!

47:50.368 --> 47:52.035
What happened with Carl?

47:52.119 --> 47:54.287
I got rid of him!
I caught him
red handed!

47:54.372 --> 47:56.790
God knows what else
he's been stealing
from me, Bernie!

47:56.874 --> 47:58.708
He says he was
gonna get it fixed.

47:58.793 --> 48:00.502
- That's what he says.
- Well, I don't think Carl...

48:00.586 --> 48:03.755
And those flowers
he's supposedly planted,

48:03.839 --> 48:05.882
they were supposed
to bloom two weeks ago.

48:05.967 --> 48:08.927
He's a lazy good fer nothin'.
The man's never done anything!

48:09.011 --> 48:11.888
I don't think
that he would ever
do anything like...

48:11.973 --> 48:14.307
Why are you stickin'
up for his kind?

48:14.392 --> 48:17.602
Marjorie, you're making it
very hard to be your friend.

48:17.687 --> 48:19.104
I'm gonna come back
some other time.

48:19.188 --> 48:21.273
Oh, just go ahead,
desert me.

48:21.357 --> 48:23.275
Just like everybody else,
go ahead, go ahead,
go ahead, go ahead.

48:23.359 --> 48:25.235
Go, go, go!
You hate me!

48:25.319 --> 48:27.821
Marjorie, I am not
going to take part

48:27.905 --> 48:30.073
in this argument.
You know [inaudible].

48:30.157 --> 48:32.450
- I know you hate me!
- No!

48:32.535 --> 48:34.327
Like everybody else!

48:34.412 --> 48:35.412
[Tires screeching]

48:35.496 --> 48:39.291
[Whimpering]

48:39.375 --> 48:40.667
[Click]

48:45.590 --> 48:46.590
Oh.

48:53.431 --> 48:56.641
Basically, it was
like Bernie became
her property.

48:56.726 --> 49:01.229
You'll never leave me.
Never.

49:01.314 --> 49:04.482
He was her sole source
of entertainment,

49:04.567 --> 49:06.693
had to do everything for her.

49:06.777 --> 49:09.529
I truly believe
the guy felt he
was smothered, choked,

49:09.614 --> 49:11.239
unable to get his wind.

49:11.324 --> 49:15.368
I don't know
how the guy
stood it. Well.

49:15.453 --> 49:17.370
Come on, just pull
the damn trigger.

49:17.455 --> 49:19.372
I don't think
I can. It doesn't
feel aimed right.

49:19.457 --> 49:20.874
Look, look,
all I want

49:20.958 --> 49:22.375
is for you to
shoot that armadillo

49:22.460 --> 49:24.461
that is digging
up my garden, okay?

49:24.545 --> 49:26.254
I mean, is that too
much for me to ask,

49:26.339 --> 49:28.715
for you to be a man
for once in your life?

49:28.799 --> 49:30.717
[Shout]

49:30.801 --> 49:32.886
Fine.

49:32.970 --> 49:35.138
Now I'm holding
you responsible

49:35.222 --> 49:38.850
for anything getting
dug up in my garden.

49:38.934 --> 49:41.978
Okay? You go out and
fix those holes yourself.

49:42.063 --> 49:45.690
Dig one
you can fit in.

49:45.775 --> 49:49.069
Let me see.

49:49.153 --> 49:51.363
Did you go
by the cleaners
to pick up my dress?

49:51.447 --> 49:52.906
Yes, earlier.

49:52.990 --> 49:54.407
Did you lysol
my kitchen counters?

49:54.492 --> 49:56.409
Mm-hm.

49:56.494 --> 49:57.911
Did you pick up
the Preparation H
from the pharmacy?

49:57.995 --> 50:00.121
No, but I figured
we'd go by there

50:00.206 --> 50:01.581
on the way to lunch.
Do you still want to
go to Jalapeño Treat?

50:01.666 --> 50:04.959
- I guess.
- Okay, hold still.

50:05.044 --> 50:06.294
Jeez.

50:06.379 --> 50:07.712
Will you be attending

50:07.797 --> 50:10.465
our dress
rehearsal tonight?

50:10.549 --> 50:11.758
No.

50:39.704 --> 50:41.121
[Gunshot]

51:02.560 --> 51:05.270
Marjorie?

51:05.354 --> 51:07.647
Marjorie, are
you okay?

51:07.732 --> 51:09.482
Marjorie, say
something to me.

51:09.567 --> 51:11.317
Marjorie, can
you talk to me?

51:11.402 --> 51:12.652
Marjorie, can you
say something?

51:12.737 --> 51:14.279
Oh no, no,
no, no, no!

51:14.363 --> 51:18.575
Oh, Jesus, no, no,
no, what have I done?

51:18.659 --> 51:23.246
Oh, God!
What have I done?

51:23.330 --> 51:24.831
Please tell me
what to do!

51:24.915 --> 51:27.584
I'll do whatever
you want me to do!

51:42.266 --> 51:45.977
♪ Seventy six trombones
Led the big parade ♪

51:46.061 --> 51:49.522
♪ With a hundred and ten
Cornets close at hand ♪

51:49.607 --> 51:53.526
♪ They were followed by
Rows and rows of the
Finest virtuosos ♪

51:53.611 --> 51:57.113
♪ So is the cream
Of every famous band ♪

51:57.198 --> 52:00.033
♪♪

52:11.587 --> 52:14.964
♪ Seventy six trombones
Hit the counterpoint ♪

52:15.049 --> 52:18.593
♪ While a hundred and ten
Cornets blazed the way ♪

52:18.677 --> 52:20.720
♪ To the rhythm
Of march! March! March! ♪

52:20.805 --> 52:22.514
♪ All the kids began to march ♪

52:22.598 --> 52:26.810
♪ And their marching
Still right today ♪♪

52:29.980 --> 52:31.689
Great job, everyone.

52:31.774 --> 52:33.650
It seemed like
the flags were
a little late,

52:33.734 --> 52:37.320
also I want to make
sure that those
fleahops are right.

52:37.404 --> 52:39.280
Now I got off that time

52:39.365 --> 52:40.740
but I feel like I got off
because one of you
got off.

52:40.825 --> 52:42.659
But it was
a really great job.

52:42.743 --> 52:44.911
Take five,
we're gonna take
it again from the top.

52:44.995 --> 52:46.663
I don't think too many of us

52:46.747 --> 52:49.123
ever asked very many questions

52:49.208 --> 52:51.960
about Mrs. Nugent,
and if we did,

52:52.044 --> 52:54.921
he would always have
a very plausible explanation.

52:55.005 --> 52:57.298
Hello, Billy,
this is Bernie Tiede

52:57.383 --> 53:00.218
calling on behalf
of Mrs. Nugent.

53:00.302 --> 53:03.513
Yes, yes, she missed her
holiday haircut appointment

53:03.597 --> 53:07.809
but she's asked me
to tell you that she
won't be coming back in.

53:07.893 --> 53:12.063
She wants to try
someone else.

53:12.147 --> 53:14.148
Well, I'm sorry
to say this

53:14.233 --> 53:19.028
but she says
that you take too long
and charge too much.

53:19.113 --> 53:22.031
Billy, I'm sorry,
but I'm just
the messenger.

53:22.116 --> 53:25.535
I was rather devastated
at the very idea

53:25.619 --> 53:28.413
that she was not
coming anymore
after 30 years

53:28.497 --> 53:31.666
of being her
friend, hairdresser,

53:31.750 --> 53:35.211
confidante sometimes,

53:35.296 --> 53:38.298
and she just
was gonna vanish.

53:38.382 --> 53:41.009
(male voice)
It was easy
for her to disappear.

53:41.093 --> 53:42.677
Nobody was looking for her.

53:42.761 --> 53:45.471
Not her son,
not her two sisters.

53:45.556 --> 53:47.307
One of them
lived here in Carthage.

53:47.391 --> 53:49.309
They hadn't spoken
in about 10 years.

53:49.393 --> 53:51.811
You want to sign
this for Mrs. Nugent,

53:51.896 --> 53:53.646
our generous benefactor?

53:53.731 --> 53:55.315
Only person
looking for her
was her stockbroker.

53:55.399 --> 53:58.234
[Phone rings]

53:58.319 --> 54:01.487
Oh, God.

54:01.572 --> 54:02.614
Hello?

54:02.698 --> 54:04.324
Bernie?
Bernie!

54:04.408 --> 54:06.200
Wh... where's Marjorie?

54:06.285 --> 54:07.493
I... I... I haven't
spoken to her in
over five weeks,

54:07.578 --> 54:09.829
I've left 11 messages.

54:09.914 --> 54:11.831
She's with me
right now, Lloyd,

54:11.916 --> 54:13.499
and I'm
sorry I couldn't
tell you earlier

54:13.584 --> 54:15.668
but she's had a series
of small strokes.

54:15.753 --> 54:18.671
I've been meaning
to call you and let
you know her situation.

54:18.756 --> 54:23.968
Mm-hm. No, she should
not be attempting to talk. No.

54:24.053 --> 54:26.262
No, you can't talk.
The doctor said...

54:26.347 --> 54:30.475
She's indicating for me
to tell you hi from her.

54:30.559 --> 54:32.393
He sends you
all his best.

54:32.478 --> 54:34.312
[Sighs]
Okay, well,

54:34.396 --> 54:36.522
we'll be in touch
when she's feeling better.

54:36.607 --> 54:38.149
I n the meantime,
let me know

54:38.233 --> 54:40.151
if I can help you
with anything. Okay.

54:40.235 --> 54:43.988
Okay, bye-bye.

54:44.073 --> 54:46.866
Bernie knew better
than touch my accounts.

54:46.951 --> 54:49.994
But he was going after
what would go into her
bank accounts

54:50.079 --> 54:51.871
because that's where
all the royalty checks went.

54:51.956 --> 54:55.458
It's usually 50,000 a month.

54:55.542 --> 54:58.044
Now he really started
being generous.

54:58.128 --> 55:02.966
He paid 5,000 dollars
for the Shreveport orchestra
to come over play the Messiah.

55:03.050 --> 55:07.470
He bought a high
dollar harpsichord
for school.

55:07.554 --> 55:10.556
He paid for the choir
to go to Russia.

55:10.641 --> 55:13.685
Well, yeah, he
hired me back
for more money,

55:13.769 --> 55:16.229
which is fine with me.

55:16.313 --> 55:18.523
Oh, he bought jet skis,

55:18.607 --> 55:20.900
he bought nine cars,

55:20.985 --> 55:23.152
he bought
struggling businesses,

55:23.237 --> 55:26.906
he paid 40,000 dollars
for Carthage Awards.

55:26.991 --> 55:28.825
That's a trophy shop.

55:28.909 --> 55:31.869
He loaned the money
to the Yokums over here,

55:31.954 --> 55:34.122
that opened up
Boot Scootin
Western Wear.

55:34.206 --> 55:37.583
I guess that was
Carthage's answer
to Neiman's.

55:37.668 --> 55:40.837
Bernie just told everybody
to pay him back when
they could.

55:40.921 --> 55:42.588
You know,
pay me when you can.

55:42.673 --> 55:44.465
But they never did.

55:44.550 --> 55:46.592
Bernie knew my twin girls'
birthday was coming up,

55:46.677 --> 55:48.177
and he thought
they should have

55:48.262 --> 55:51.097
a big nice
playhouse, you know?

55:51.181 --> 55:53.266
Little girls.

55:53.350 --> 55:57.437
Bernie bought this
playhouse for my girls.

56:00.274 --> 56:05.528
Oh.
[Chuckling]

56:05.612 --> 56:09.574
Thank you.

56:09.658 --> 56:12.368
I just feel like I need to say,
Bernie Tiede, God bless
you, son.

56:12.453 --> 56:15.329
You've done more to transform
the town of Carthage
than anyone else.

56:15.414 --> 56:21.294
- Oh, thank you.
- God bless you, Bernie.

56:21.378 --> 56:24.797
Bernie could've bought a
mansion for himself
with the money.

56:24.882 --> 56:27.467
But he kept
that little house

56:27.551 --> 56:29.802
worth, maybe, 50,000.

56:29.887 --> 56:33.473
Now he bought cars
for folks that needed it.

56:33.557 --> 56:36.142
And he paid cash for those.

56:36.226 --> 56:39.645
But that old Lincoln
he was drivin'?

56:39.730 --> 56:41.481
He had it financed.

56:41.565 --> 56:45.234
And he was
usually behind
on his payments.

56:45.319 --> 56:48.112
No, there really
wasn't any greed
in him.

56:48.197 --> 56:51.032
Almost everything he
got from Mrs. Nugent,

56:51.116 --> 56:53.826
he gave to somebody else.

57:03.629 --> 57:07.298
Lloyd seems to be
pretty concerned.

57:07.382 --> 57:09.300
He thinks the family
should get involved.

57:09.384 --> 57:12.386
Oh, good lord,
you gotta be
kidding me.

57:12.471 --> 57:15.181
I don't know why
Lloyd is so paranoid.

57:15.265 --> 57:17.100
It's like I told him.

57:17.184 --> 57:19.352
She's at the Scott White
Nursing Home in Temple.

57:19.436 --> 57:22.355
She didn't want
everyone to know,

57:22.439 --> 57:24.690
'cause she's afraid
the family would
come in

57:24.775 --> 57:26.275
and try to take
over her affairs.

57:26.360 --> 57:29.028
That sounds
just like Marjorie.

57:29.113 --> 57:31.447
Mm-hm. That's
Marjorie alright.

57:31.532 --> 57:33.783
- Mm-hm.
- One hundred percent.

57:33.867 --> 57:37.203
You know, Bernie,
she's my sister,

57:37.287 --> 57:39.580
and I guess that
I should love her.

57:39.665 --> 57:41.124
But she's just mean.

57:41.208 --> 57:43.668
She's just hard down mean.

57:43.752 --> 57:46.462
Mm. Well, there's some
goodness in there, too.

57:46.547 --> 57:48.506
She used to tear
up my toys,

57:48.590 --> 57:51.050
she pulled the heads
off my dolls,

57:51.135 --> 57:54.220
she used to tear up
my homework.

57:54.304 --> 58:04.313
And next up
is Mrs. Ida Parker.

58:04.398 --> 58:07.900
Ida says she does not
like knitting, crocheting,

58:07.985 --> 58:10.278
gardening, cooking
fancy food,

58:10.362 --> 58:13.406
excessive housework,
or artsy hobbies.

58:13.490 --> 58:16.409
She's planning on doing
these things when she
gets old.

58:16.493 --> 58:18.077
[Audience laughs]

58:18.162 --> 58:21.873
♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪

58:21.957 --> 58:24.625
♪ Queen of my song ♪

58:24.710 --> 58:27.795
♪ List while I woo thee ♪

58:27.880 --> 58:33.926
♪ With soft melody ♪

58:34.011 --> 58:37.722
♪ Gone are the cares of ♪

58:37.806 --> 58:41.267
♪ Life's busy throng ♪

58:41.351 --> 58:43.644
♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪

58:43.729 --> 58:48.566
♪ Awake to my song ♪

58:48.650 --> 58:51.235
♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪

58:51.320 --> 58:56.032
♪ Awake unto me ♪

58:56.116 --> 58:57.783
♪♪

58:57.868 --> 59:02.288
♪ Beautiful dreamer ♪

59:02.372 --> 59:09.253
♪ Awaken to me ♪

59:09.338 --> 59:11.631
♪♪

59:11.715 --> 59:12.632
[audience claps]

59:12.716 --> 59:18.221
Thank you.

59:18.305 --> 59:21.098
So you saw Mrs. Nugent
in April of this year?

59:21.183 --> 59:23.142
You know, I believe
it was April.

59:23.227 --> 59:25.770
With your own eyes?

59:25.854 --> 59:29.357
Well, you know,
I didn't actually... see
her that day, I...

59:29.441 --> 59:32.985
I came to her house
to get her to sign
some documents.

59:33.070 --> 59:35.947
Bernie comes to the door,
says she's feeling poorly.

59:36.031 --> 59:38.991
Just then, he takes
the documents back
and she signs them.

59:39.076 --> 59:40.826
I go on
about my business.

59:40.911 --> 59:44.664
Okay. It
confirms a pattern.

59:44.748 --> 59:46.123
I appreciate it.

59:47.876 --> 59:50.002
Well, it sounds like
Lloyd Hornbuckle

59:50.087 --> 59:51.837
called Wayne Junior
up in Amarillo,

59:51.922 --> 59:53.464
and got him
all riled up.

59:53.548 --> 59:55.675
Oh, boy.

59:55.759 --> 59:57.593
You know, I think
Lloyd's just upset

59:57.678 --> 59:59.637
because he's
losing commissions
during her illness.

59:59.721 --> 01:00:01.681
He can't move
Mrs. Nugent's
money around

01:00:01.765 --> 01:00:04.350
and keep taking
his commissions the
way he's used to, so...

01:00:04.434 --> 01:00:06.686
It may be so, but
Dwayne Junior says
his money

01:00:06.770 --> 01:00:10.273
comes in every year
for his kids from
his dad's will.

01:00:10.357 --> 01:00:12.275
It hadn't come
in this year.

01:00:12.359 --> 01:00:13.859
And it won't
until Mrs. Nugent's
in better condition

01:00:13.944 --> 01:00:15.278
to take care of such things.

01:00:15.362 --> 01:00:16.696
The poor lady's
in the hospital

01:00:16.780 --> 01:00:18.322
having suffered
a major stroke.

01:00:18.407 --> 01:00:20.283
She simply doesn't
want to be disturbed.

01:00:20.367 --> 01:00:22.535
Tell everyone
for heaven's sake,

01:00:22.619 --> 01:00:24.203
to please have
a little more patience.

01:00:24.288 --> 01:00:25.788
Well, that's
fine with me.

01:00:25.872 --> 01:00:27.164
I don't want her
disturbing me,

01:00:27.249 --> 01:00:31.294
if you wanna
know the truth.

01:00:31.378 --> 01:00:33.546
I'm sorry you had
to get wrapped up
in all this.

01:00:33.630 --> 01:00:36.882
Oh, forget about it,
Lloyd Hornbuckle's
just a busybody.

01:00:36.967 --> 01:00:39.593
- I'll see you later, Bernie.
- Thank you, Sheriff.

01:00:41.972 --> 01:00:43.222
[Cell ringing]

01:00:52.232 --> 01:00:53.858
Hello.

01:00:53.942 --> 01:00:56.569
(LIoyd)
You are living
in a wold of guilt.

01:00:56.653 --> 01:01:00.614
All the police have to do
is find one shred
of evidence

01:01:00.699 --> 01:01:04.118
and it's off
to hell you go.

01:01:04.202 --> 01:01:06.287
Lloyd, is that you?

01:01:06.371 --> 01:01:09.332
Lloyd? Hello...

01:01:09.416 --> 01:01:13.294
[sigh]

01:01:13.378 --> 01:01:14.837
Bernie, are
you okay?

01:01:14.921 --> 01:01:18.799
Hm? Yeah,
I just, uh...

01:01:18.884 --> 01:01:20.593
[deep sigh]

01:01:20.677 --> 01:01:22.053
Can I ask
you something?

01:01:22.137 --> 01:01:23.596
Of course.

01:01:23.680 --> 01:01:27.183
It's so strange.

01:01:27.267 --> 01:01:32.772
Do you believe
a person could
be capable of...

01:01:32.856 --> 01:01:35.107
an action...

01:01:35.192 --> 01:01:36.525
and yet to them
it feels like

01:01:36.610 --> 01:01:37.902
it's not even
them doing it.

01:01:37.986 --> 01:01:42.782
Almost like
Jekyll and Hyde?

01:01:42.866 --> 01:01:47.203
Bernie, stop worrying,
it's okay.

01:01:47.287 --> 01:01:52.291
Someone's personal
proclivities are
nobody's else's business.

01:01:52.376 --> 01:01:58.798
We all love you like
you are, Bernie,
no matter what.

01:01:58.882 --> 01:02:05.179
♪ Shackled by a heavy burden ♪

01:02:05.263 --> 01:02:10.810
♪ B'neath the load
Of guilt and shame ♪

01:02:10.894 --> 01:02:16.148
♪ Then the hand
Of Jesus touched me ♪

01:02:16.233 --> 01:02:22.071
♪ And now I am
No longer the same ♪

01:02:22.155 --> 01:02:25.324
♪ He touched me,
Oh he touched me ♪

01:02:25.409 --> 01:02:29.620
- God bless you, Bernie.
- God bless you, Mr. Brown.

01:02:29.704 --> 01:02:32.123
- That was beautiful.
- Thank you.

01:02:32.207 --> 01:02:34.959
- You have a blessed weekend.
- God bless you too.

01:02:35.043 --> 01:02:36.544
Thank you.

01:02:36.628 --> 01:02:38.045
As always, Bernie,
I love the songs.

01:02:38.130 --> 01:02:39.964
- Thank you.
- My sympathies.

01:02:40.048 --> 01:02:41.632
Thank you, Mari Belle,
it's always great to
see you.

01:02:41.716 --> 01:02:43.509
I'm so sorry
Marjorie didn't hear that,

01:02:43.593 --> 01:02:45.928
I hear she's doing better.

01:02:46.012 --> 01:02:50.599
Yes, some days
it seems she's starting
to feel better but, um...

01:02:50.684 --> 01:02:52.518
I'm still afraid...

01:02:52.602 --> 01:02:54.186
I'm gonna lose
her soon.

01:02:54.271 --> 01:02:56.188
[Cooing sounds]

01:03:01.403 --> 01:03:03.529
(Lloyd, off)
Finally.

01:03:03.613 --> 01:03:06.866
Nine months
since I had last laid
eyes on Mrs. Nugent,

01:03:06.950 --> 01:03:08.617
we got
into her house.

01:03:08.702 --> 01:03:09.660
Grandma?

