seeking a change
of venue

01:17:03.703 --> 01:17:06.204
because the defendant
was so well liked

01:17:06.289 --> 01:17:08.665
that they couldn't
get a conviction.

01:17:08.749 --> 01:17:14.045
So when I heard that
the judge had actually
agreed to move the trial,

01:17:14.130 --> 01:17:19.092
giving in to Danny Buck's
harebrained request,

01:17:19.176 --> 01:17:22.762
my first thought
was, "Oh, shit.

01:17:22.847 --> 01:17:25.181
Our donkey's in a ditch."

01:17:25.266 --> 01:17:28.059
♪♪

01:17:28.144 --> 01:17:29.686
Bring in the freezer.

01:17:32.231 --> 01:17:34.858
Let the jury be able to see

01:17:34.942 --> 01:17:40.905
where Mrs. Nugent spent
the first nine months
of her afterlife.

01:17:40.990 --> 01:17:43.241
A poor excuse for a casket.

01:17:43.326 --> 01:17:46.244
Boys, make sure
it opens up
to the jury.

01:17:46.329 --> 01:17:49.914
There's some wild shit
on both sides
of the courtroom.

01:17:49.999 --> 01:17:52.584
But, you know,
this was the big stage

01:17:52.668 --> 01:17:56.046
the big town,
the big show they'd
been waiting for

01:17:56.130 --> 01:17:57.797
and they pulled
out all the stops.

01:17:57.882 --> 01:18:01.593
They wheeled in
the actual deep freeze.

01:18:01.677 --> 01:18:07.515
Mm-hm.

01:18:07.600 --> 01:18:13.021
They projected pictures
of frozen dead
Mrs. Nugent.

01:18:13.105 --> 01:18:17.275
And then they started
bringing out the crying
weeping relatives.

01:18:17.360 --> 01:18:19.861
And then I went
to the freezer.

01:18:19.945 --> 01:18:21.446
And I saw

01:18:21.530 --> 01:18:25.450
underneath her corn
and her steak and...

01:18:25.534 --> 01:18:28.203
her pot pies was...

01:18:28.287 --> 01:18:32.457
the top of her head.

01:18:32.541 --> 01:18:34.000
It was so horrible.

01:18:38.714 --> 01:18:40.382
No further questions,
Your Honor.

01:18:44.053 --> 01:18:46.805
When was the last
time you talked
to your grandmother?

01:18:46.889 --> 01:18:50.475
U m, I don't remember.

01:18:50.559 --> 01:18:52.185
Isn't it true that
you and your brother

01:18:52.269 --> 01:18:56.815
sued your grandmother
almost four years ago?

01:18:56.899 --> 01:18:59.275
We were advised
to by a lawyer.

01:18:59.360 --> 01:19:01.236
A lawyer?

01:19:01.320 --> 01:19:06.074
You mean, just some
old boy come in off
the street?

01:19:06.158 --> 01:19:09.202
Or are we talking
about your lawyer?

01:19:09.286 --> 01:19:11.996
I guess he was
working for us.

01:19:12.081 --> 01:19:14.582
I'll say he was
working for you.

01:19:14.667 --> 01:19:18.002
He was trying to get
your grandmother's
money, wasn't he?

01:19:21.799 --> 01:19:26.177
Did you ever speak
to her after that?

01:19:26.262 --> 01:19:27.470
I don't think so.

01:19:27.555 --> 01:19:29.055
Oh, you don't
think so.

01:19:29.140 --> 01:19:31.641
Well, you know
you didn't.

01:19:31.725 --> 01:19:34.644
But you told us earlier
that you were real close
to your grandmother.

01:19:34.728 --> 01:19:37.981
Now was that the same
woman you were suing
for money?

01:19:38.065 --> 01:19:40.191
Is that the same woman

01:19:40.276 --> 01:19:44.195
that you have
not spoken to
in four years?

01:19:44.280 --> 01:19:47.782
I felt in our hearts
we were still close.

01:19:47.867 --> 01:19:50.368
[Scoffs]

01:19:50.453 --> 01:19:51.786
I knew he
was in trouble

01:19:51.871 --> 01:19:54.247
when I saw
that jury.

01:19:54.331 --> 01:19:57.834
And Bernie was just gonna
have to get up there and
explain himself

01:19:57.918 --> 01:20:02.422
to a bunch of Saint Augustine
cousin-countin' rednecks
over there.

01:20:02.506 --> 01:20:05.592
I mean, they got more
tattoos than teeth

01:20:05.676 --> 01:20:08.553
and there ain't
no brain in the
whole dozen of 'em,

01:20:08.637 --> 01:20:10.722
and they're supposed
to decide

01:20:10.806 --> 01:20:13.266
big things like this?

01:20:13.350 --> 01:20:17.896
I mean, shoot,
I wouldn't let 'em
work on my car.

01:20:17.980 --> 01:20:20.398
Now, Bernie,

01:20:20.483 --> 01:20:23.485
after you
were arrested you gave
a confession, correct?

01:20:23.569 --> 01:20:26.571
Yes, sir.

01:20:26.655 --> 01:20:30.366
How did you feel
about Marjorie Nugent?

01:20:30.451 --> 01:20:33.036
I cared for Marjorie deeply.

01:20:33.120 --> 01:20:35.371
I loved her very much.

01:20:35.456 --> 01:20:37.207
And I've sent letters
from jail to her family

01:20:37.291 --> 01:20:41.586
asking their forgiveness
for ruining Margy's life

01:20:41.670 --> 01:20:44.923
and the pain
I've caused.

01:20:45.007 --> 01:20:47.300
Well, if you
cared for her,

01:20:47.384 --> 01:20:50.094
even loved her,

01:20:50.179 --> 01:20:53.097
why do you reckon
you killed her?

01:20:53.182 --> 01:20:54.974
[Deep sigh]

01:20:55.059 --> 01:20:56.476
I could probably
describe it like
being in prison

01:20:56.560 --> 01:20:59.562
to some degree.

01:20:59.647 --> 01:21:01.523
She wouldn't allow me
to have any friends,

01:21:01.607 --> 01:21:04.734
and I'm a people
person. I got
to have my friends.

01:21:04.818 --> 01:21:06.528
[Sigh]

01:21:06.612 --> 01:21:11.407
She was very jealous
and possessive of my time.

01:21:11.492 --> 01:21:15.787
She had become
so hateful.

01:21:15.871 --> 01:21:18.623
I don't even remember
picking up the gun
that day.

01:21:18.707 --> 01:21:21.626
It was like
someone else
was doing it.

01:21:21.710 --> 01:21:24.128
So why did you
leave the body there?

01:21:24.213 --> 01:21:26.130
It would seem
to me that

01:21:26.215 --> 01:21:28.132
if you didn't
want to get caught,

01:21:28.217 --> 01:21:30.426
you'd find some way
to dispose of it.

01:21:30.511 --> 01:21:31.803
Oh no, no, no.

01:21:31.887 --> 01:21:34.138
I could never do that.

01:21:34.223 --> 01:21:35.932
That was never my intention.

01:21:36.016 --> 01:21:38.309
Everyone deserves
a proper burial.

01:21:38.394 --> 01:21:40.687
And I was...

01:21:40.771 --> 01:21:43.982
I was just waiting
for my chance
to give her one.

01:21:52.950 --> 01:21:54.993
Thank you, Bernie.

01:21:55.077 --> 01:21:58.371
I'll pass the witness.

01:21:58.455 --> 01:22:01.916
So help me
out here, Bernie.

01:22:02.001 --> 01:22:07.505
On this trip
with Mrs. Nugent
to New York City,

01:22:07.590 --> 01:22:12.468
did you fly
first class?

01:22:12.553 --> 01:22:15.013
Yes, I believe
we did.

01:22:15.097 --> 01:22:17.515
Tell us the difference
between like the first
class seats

01:22:17.600 --> 01:22:19.684
and the regular old seats
in the back of the plane.

01:22:19.768 --> 01:22:22.687
I... I've never
been up there.

01:22:22.771 --> 01:22:25.523
I'd say the seats
are a little larger maybe.

01:22:25.608 --> 01:22:27.692
More comfortable.

01:22:27.776 --> 01:22:30.236
Don't they have people
waiting' on you and stuff
too, you know?

01:22:30.321 --> 01:22:32.697
I mean, people
bringing you fancy food,

01:22:32.781 --> 01:22:36.951
and serving you
whatever you want to
drink and stuff like that?

01:22:37.036 --> 01:22:40.288
Yes, the service
is probably a little better.

01:22:40.372 --> 01:22:42.665
Oh, so you like the
first class treatment.

01:22:42.750 --> 01:22:48.421
First class lifestyle,
the best that money
can buy.

01:22:48.505 --> 01:22:50.381
I was accompanying
Mrs. Nugent

01:22:50.466 --> 01:22:52.425
who usually
preferred these things
when she traveled.

01:22:52.509 --> 01:22:54.510
- Mm-hm.
- So.

01:22:54.595 --> 01:22:57.889
Now, on that
New York City trip,

01:22:57.973 --> 01:22:59.724
it says here that
you and Mrs. Nugent

01:22:59.808 --> 01:23:05.355
stayed at the...
the Ritz Carlton?

01:23:05.439 --> 01:23:09.067
That's a fancy hotel
near Central Park,
isn't it?

01:23:09.151 --> 01:23:12.070
Yes, I believe that
is where we stayed.

01:23:12.154 --> 01:23:14.989
It also says here
that while you were
in New York City,

01:23:15.074 --> 01:23:17.367
you saw an opera.

01:23:17.451 --> 01:23:19.285
And a Broadway play.

01:23:19.370 --> 01:23:22.413
I think it's called
"Les Miserables."

01:23:22.498 --> 01:23:27.752
[French accent]
Les Miserable.

01:23:27.836 --> 01:23:31.422
That's impressive.

01:23:31.507 --> 01:23:32.965
What?

01:23:33.050 --> 01:23:36.761
So culture
is important to you.

01:23:36.845 --> 01:23:38.721
I n what way?

01:23:38.806 --> 01:23:41.557
Well, you seem to know
all these fancy words
and such.

01:23:41.642 --> 01:23:43.768
Well, that one's
not very difficult.

01:23:43.852 --> 01:23:48.106
[Laughter]

01:23:48.190 --> 01:23:53.569
Not for you.

01:23:53.654 --> 01:23:57.740
You know all about
the high class life,
don't you?

01:23:57.825 --> 01:24:02.620
I... what... like what?

01:24:02.705 --> 01:24:05.998
Like, I don't know,
say for instance what...

01:24:06.083 --> 01:24:10.795
what kind of wine
are you supposed
to have with fish?

01:24:10.879 --> 01:24:13.881
No, I don't...
white usually.

01:24:13.966 --> 01:24:18.302
Mm-hm. That takes
a lot of money

01:24:18.387 --> 01:24:20.471
to have so much
culture, don't it?

01:24:20.556 --> 01:24:23.099
To... to enjoy the finer
things in life

01:24:23.183 --> 01:24:25.184
that you love
so much.

01:24:25.269 --> 01:24:28.938
The ritzy hotels,
first class flying
off to the big cities.

01:24:29.022 --> 01:24:31.065
I mean, it takes
a lot of money

01:24:31.150 --> 01:24:32.650
to live that
way, don't it?

01:24:32.735 --> 01:24:34.652
No, I... left
to my own devices,

01:24:34.737 --> 01:24:36.612
I would not
have been traveling
in such an expensive...

01:24:36.697 --> 01:24:38.990
But left to someone
else's devices,
you were!

01:24:39.074 --> 01:24:41.534
And after you killed
Mrs. Nugent,

01:24:41.618 --> 01:24:43.453
you kept on spending
her money, didn't you?

01:24:43.537 --> 01:24:45.455
A lot of it!

01:24:45.539 --> 01:24:47.415
And if you wouldn't
a been caught,

01:24:47.499 --> 01:24:50.001
you'd still be
spending her
money today.

01:24:50.085 --> 01:24:51.461
Wouldn't you?

01:24:51.545 --> 01:24:54.714
Wouldn't you?

01:24:54.798 --> 01:24:58.176
[Thud with hand]

01:24:58.260 --> 01:25:00.720
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:25:00.804 --> 01:25:03.681
after listening to
all the evidence,

01:25:03.766 --> 01:25:06.058
I'm sure that
you will agree

01:25:06.143 --> 01:25:10.980
that the defendant
is a liar, a coward

01:25:11.064 --> 01:25:15.026
and a backshooter.

01:25:15.110 --> 01:25:17.695
Now, come on.

01:25:17.780 --> 01:25:19.572
That's got to be
about the lowest thing

01:25:19.656 --> 01:25:23.576
a man could ever do,
ain't it?

01:25:23.660 --> 01:25:26.871
Shoot a little old
lady in the back?

01:25:26.955 --> 01:25:30.458
Four times.

01:25:30.542 --> 01:25:33.085
There is no doubt
in my mind

01:25:33.170 --> 01:25:38.090
Bernie Tiede is
a calculating
evil actor.

01:25:38.175 --> 01:25:40.635
He fooled a whole town

01:25:40.719 --> 01:25:43.262
for nine months.

01:25:43.347 --> 01:25:45.264
Now if he can do that,

01:25:45.349 --> 01:25:46.849
there ain't no telling
what he'll do

01:25:46.934 --> 01:25:49.060
if you let him
back on the streets.

01:25:53.440 --> 01:25:59.570
That poor woman stayed
frozen stiff for nine
whole months.

01:25:59.655 --> 01:26:03.282
I n a freezer.

01:26:03.367 --> 01:26:07.578
It took two days
to thaw her out.

01:26:07.663 --> 01:26:11.666
Just so they could
perform a proper autopsy.

01:26:11.750 --> 01:26:17.088
No.
No, no, no, no, no.

01:26:17.172 --> 01:26:18.714
I'm sorry.

01:26:22.344 --> 01:26:28.057
Your honor, counsel,
ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

01:26:28.141 --> 01:26:31.060
all Danny Buck Davidson
wants to do in this trial

01:26:31.144 --> 01:26:34.897
is get you to believe
that Bernie is some
kind of monster.

01:26:34.982 --> 01:26:39.902
That he is
something other than
a fellow human being.

01:26:39.987 --> 01:26:41.821
Look at him,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:26:41.905 --> 01:26:45.992
There is not one hint
of premeditation
in this case.

01:26:46.076 --> 01:26:49.120
If there was, he'd have
done it a lot differently.

01:26:49.204 --> 01:26:51.330
He mighta
gotten away with it.

01:26:51.415 --> 01:26:55.459
Did he try to poison
her slowly? No.

01:26:55.544 --> 01:26:57.628
Did he burn
down the house?

01:26:57.713 --> 01:27:01.257
Say it was an
accidental fire? No.

01:27:01.341 --> 01:27:02.842
He still knew
he done wrong.

01:27:02.926 --> 01:27:04.385
He knew he was gonna
get found out.

01:27:04.469 --> 01:27:06.178
He just didn't have
the courage

01:27:06.263 --> 01:27:08.139
to tell on himself.

01:27:08.223 --> 01:27:10.266
But like a good
funeral director,

01:27:10.350 --> 01:27:15.438
he preserved the body
so that she could have
a proper burial.

01:27:15.522 --> 01:27:21.736
And in the meantime
he did a lot of good
for a lot of people.

01:27:21.820 --> 01:27:26.908
Till he finally
got caught.

01:27:26.992 --> 01:27:31.329
He just doesn't sound
like any kind of monster
I've ever heard of.

01:27:31.413 --> 01:27:33.623
Thank you.

01:27:33.707 --> 01:27:35.082
[Lively chatter]

01:27:44.134 --> 01:27:47.011
(Danny)
That doesn't excuse
the crime that was committed.

01:27:47.095 --> 01:27:50.097
Now look, everybody's
describing Bernie Tiede
as such a great guy.

01:27:50.182 --> 01:27:52.850
"Oh, he's
so wonderful.
He's an angel."

01:27:52.935 --> 01:27:54.685
Let me tell you,
he's an angel alright.

01:27:54.770 --> 01:27:58.356
An angel of death.

01:27:58.440 --> 01:27:59.899
Thank you.

01:28:31.682 --> 01:28:39.146
(male voice)
Bernie Tiede,
please rise.

01:28:39.231 --> 01:28:42.024
Mr. Foreman, it
is my understanding

01:28:42.109 --> 01:28:44.443
that the jury
has reached a verdict.

01:28:44.528 --> 01:28:47.238
Yes, sir,
we have,
Your Honor.

01:28:47.322 --> 01:28:49.365
Is it unanimous?

01:28:49.449 --> 01:28:50.866
Yes, sir.

01:28:50.951 --> 01:28:57.123
Would you please
read the verdict?

01:28:57.207 --> 01:29:00.584
[Clears throat]

01:29:00.669 --> 01:29:02.253
We, the jury,

01:29:02.337 --> 01:29:04.880
find the defendant
Bernie Tiede,

01:29:04.965 --> 01:29:07.425
guilty of murder
as charged.

01:29:07.509 --> 01:29:08.592
[Gasping]

01:29:41.418 --> 01:29:43.461
(Bernie)
They gave me life.

01:29:43.545 --> 01:29:49.216
I won't even be
up for parole
for 50 years.

01:29:49.301 --> 01:29:51.010
I'll be 89 years old.

01:29:53.722 --> 01:29:55.639
Danny Buck,
you gotta hand
it to him.

01:29:55.724 --> 01:29:59.393
What he did,
is two groups, you know.

01:29:59.478 --> 01:30:01.979
It was
the high-falutin'
first class livin'

01:30:02.064 --> 01:30:04.148
Bernies of the world,

01:30:04.232 --> 01:30:06.275
and then there was
the, you know,

01:30:06.359 --> 01:30:10.571
let's dig a hole in
the backyard and cook
something, you know?

01:30:10.655 --> 01:30:15.159
Put another tire
on the fire, George.
I'm cold.

01:30:15.243 --> 01:30:17.203
It was just
two different worlds
he created there

01:30:17.287 --> 01:30:21.791
and Bernie wasn't
of their world.

01:30:21.875 --> 01:30:27.838
[Soft murmuring]

01:30:27.923 --> 01:30:29.673
(Bernie)
It's not as bad
as you think.

01:30:29.758 --> 01:30:34.512
I'm the choir director,
teaching four classes.

01:30:34.596 --> 01:30:37.223
I'm in the craft shop
most of the day.

01:30:37.307 --> 01:30:38.516
I miss my freedom.

01:30:38.600 --> 01:30:40.810
Well, sure
you do, hon.

01:30:40.894 --> 01:30:42.520
I'm making
the best of it.

01:30:42.604 --> 01:30:44.188
Got a lot
to live for.

01:30:44.272 --> 01:30:46.398
You do.
You do.

01:30:46.483 --> 01:30:47.817
I wanna help
people here.

01:30:47.901 --> 01:30:49.860
[Shouting]

01:30:49.945 --> 01:30:52.446
Hm, well, I have
to tell you what
I've done.

01:30:52.531 --> 01:30:54.448
I wrote the warden
a letter.

01:30:54.533 --> 01:30:56.325
Yeah, I did.

01:30:56.409 --> 01:30:58.452
I told him that he
had to give you
a work release

01:30:58.537 --> 01:31:00.412
or something like that

01:31:00.497 --> 01:31:02.790
so that you could
sing at my funeral.

01:31:02.874 --> 01:31:05.376
Now, I'm not sick
or anything, but
now Bernie,

01:31:05.460 --> 01:31:08.295
you promised me
that you would
do that.

01:31:08.380 --> 01:31:11.215
And I totally mean
wear those chains
or whatever

01:31:11.299 --> 01:31:13.717
if it made them
feel better so...

01:31:13.802 --> 01:31:16.137
That is awful
sweet, Lenora.

01:31:16.221 --> 01:31:19.014
And it would be
an honor but don't
count on it.

01:31:19.099 --> 01:31:20.307
I don't think they're
letting me out of here
for nothing.

01:31:20.392 --> 01:31:22.518
Oh!
[Pfft]

01:31:22.602 --> 01:31:25.062
Sure they will.
I told him that you
went temporarily insane.

01:31:25.147 --> 01:31:27.815
And we're all going
insane sooner or later.

01:31:27.899 --> 01:31:30.401
I mean, that's the way
I look at it.

01:31:30.485 --> 01:31:34.905
U h-oh. He's telling
me our time is up.

01:31:34.990 --> 01:31:36.782
I cannot tell you
how much it means
to me

01:31:36.867 --> 01:31:38.909
that I'm still
in your prayers.

01:31:38.994 --> 01:31:40.494
And that I'll
always be with you.

01:31:40.579 --> 01:31:43.414
Yes. And you know
how much we love you.

01:31:43.498 --> 01:31:45.583
And I will tell you,
I look around here.

01:31:45.667 --> 01:31:47.084
You need to take
care of yourself

01:31:47.169 --> 01:31:48.752
and be real careful
because I think

01:31:48.837 --> 01:31:50.588
this could be
a dangerous place.

01:31:50.672 --> 01:31:52.631
- You think?
- I do.

01:31:52.716 --> 01:31:54.592
And we'll come back
in a couple of weeks.

01:31:54.676 --> 01:31:55.759
Take care.
I love you.

01:31:55.844 --> 01:31:59.180
I love you, baby.

01:31:59.264 --> 01:32:00.681
You take
care of him.

01:32:08.190 --> 01:32:12.026
I don't care
what he did.

01:32:12.110 --> 01:32:14.612
Yes, I do care.

01:32:14.696 --> 01:32:18.032
It was wrong.

01:32:18.116 --> 01:32:23.913
But I believed that if Bernie
were truly sorry for what
he did,

01:32:23.997 --> 01:32:26.624
